      <h2 id="common-integration-mistakes">Common Integration Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>I've seen contractors waste thousands on integration projects that don't deliver results. Here are the five most expensive mistakes:</p>

        <h3>1. Integrating Too Many Tools at Once</h3>
        <p>Start with your core workflow: CRM to accounting. Get that working perfectly before adding marketing automation or advanced analytics. Companies that try to integrate 8+ tools simultaneously have a 73% failure rate.</p>

        <h3>2. Choosing Custom Development Too Early</h3>
        <p>Native integrations and Zapier handle 95% of HVAC contractor needs. Custom APIs only make sense for companies doing $5+ million annually with unique requirements.</p>

        <h3>3. Ignoring Data Quality</h3>
        <p>Integrations amplify existing data problems. Clean your customer database before connecting systems, or you'll sync duplicate records and incorrect information across all platforms.</p>

        <h3>4. Skipping User Training</h3>
        <p>The best integrations fail if your team doesn't understand the new workflows. Budget 4-6 hours of training time per employee for major integration rollouts.</p>

        <h3>5. No Backup Plan</h3>
        <p>Integrations break. Have manual processes documented for your most critical workflows (scheduling, invoicing, customer communication).</p>

        <p>Companies that avoid these mistakes see integration success rates above 90% and ROI within 90 days.</p>
      </div>

